(%i1) load(draw)$
(%i2) draw3d(color = green,
             explicit(20*exp(-x^2-y^2)-10,x,0,2,y,-3,3),
             contour_levels = [-8,4,8],
             contour        = both,
             surface_hide   = true) $
@end example

Líneas correspondientes a los niveles -7, -6, 0.8 y 5.
@example
(%i1) load(draw)$
(%i2) draw3d(color = green,
             explicit(20*exp(-x^2-y^2)-10,x,0,2,y,-3,3),
             contour_levels = @{-7, -6, 0.8, 5@},
             contour        = both,
